## Red Flag Catalog

### Immediate Credibility Concerns

- No author attribution
- No publication date
- Broken or circular citations
- Domain is content farm or known misinformation source
- Excessive advertising or clickbait design
- Claims to be "the truth they don't want you to know"
- No contact information or about page
- Recently created domain with authoritative-sounding name

### Claims That Require Extra Scrutiny

- "Studies show" without citing specific studies
- Single study presented as consensus
- Extraordinary claims (require extraordinary evidence)
- Claims that align too perfectly with partisan positions
- Statistics without source or methodology
- Anecdotes presented as evidence
- Expert quotes without verifiable attribution

